            <h2 class="display-4">Impact of Carbon Emissions on Bangalore</h2>
            <p>Carbon emissions in Bangalore have led to severe health issues and environmental challenges, affecting millions of residents:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Diseases Caused by Carbon Emissions:</b> Respiratory diseases, cardiovascular problems, and allergies are prevalent due to poor air quality caused by carbon emissions from vehicles and industries.</li>
                <li><b>Statistics of Highest Carbon Emission Years:</b> In recent years, Bangalore has experienced a significant increase in carbon emissions, especially during peak traffic hours and industrial activities.</li>
                <li><b>Environmental Effects:</b> High levels of air pollution contribute to reduced quality of life, environmental degradation, and increased healthcare costs.</li>
                <li><b>Efforts and Solutions:</b> Initiatives such as promoting electric vehicles, improving public transportation, and implementing stricter emission norms are crucial to mitigating the impact of carbon emissions in Bangalore.</li>
                <li><b>Government Initiatives:</b> The Bangalore Municipal Corporation has launched several initiatives to address pollution, including tree planting drives, pollution monitoring, and promoting sustainable development practices.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Efforts are also underway to raise awareness among citizens about the impact of carbon emissions and encourage community participation in sustainable practices.</p>
