            <p>Poor air quality in Bangalore, exacerbated by high carbon emissions, has profound health implications:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Increased cases of asthma and other respiratory diseases among residents, particularly children and the elderly.</li>
                <li>Higher incidence of cardiovascular diseases linked to long-term exposure to air pollutants.</li>
                <li>Compromised immune systems, making individuals more susceptible to infections.</li>
                <li>Impact on mental health due to stress and anxiety caused by living in a polluted environment.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Addressing air quality issues is critical to improving public health and quality of life in Bangalore.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

