            <p>Key statistics provide insights into the scale and impact of carbon emissions in Bangalore:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Highest Emission Years:</b> Recent data shows that the years 2019 and 2020 recorded the highest levels of carbon emissions due to increased vehicular traffic and industrial activities.</li>
                <li><b>Carbon Footprint per Capita:</b> Bangalore's per capita carbon footprint has risen steadily, reflecting growing urbanization and industrialization.</li>
                <li><b>Impact on Climate:</b> Local climate patterns have been affected, leading to irregular weather patterns and increased frequency of heatwaves and monsoon disruptions.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Efforts to curb emissions are crucial for mitigating climate change impacts and ensuring sustainable urban development.</p>
